<br>
The Ogre warrior can then not have to worry about getting Sta items and only concentrate on AC and HPs, where as the Halfling warrior with identical equipment as the Ogre will have less hit points (assuming that the equipment does not put both of them at 255 sta) and have to work on getting items that add sta too.<br>
<br>
Now, Agi vs Sta<br>
Agi is valuable at low levels where you are not getting as many hps per point of Sta. But even then, its 3 to 4 points of Agi to get 1 point of AC and Sta is at worst 2 hp per Sta as a warrior, so for 10 pts of either at the lowest of levels 3 AC vs 20 hps is pretty close, I guess I would lean towards the AC there.<br>
<br>
However if you ever think you are going to get to 30+ level, Sta will out strip AC, I will take 60 hps over 3 AC everyday of the week (and twice on Sunday).<br>
<br>
All of this being said, play the race you will have the most fun with <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
